      },
      "rdfs:label": "exponent of US dollar",
      "rdfs:range": {
        "@id": "xsd:decimal"
      },
      "skos:definition": "The exponent of US Dollar in a product of powers of base units.",
      "skos:example": "In the equation '1 million dollars per week = 1.65344 x dollar per second'\r\n\r\n\t\tthe conversion factor for million dollars per week is 1.65344\r\n\t\tthe exponent of US Dollar is 1\r\n\t\tthe exponent of second is -1\r\n\t\tall other exponents are zero\r\n\r\n\t\tEvery member of a unit group containing million dollars per week must be a multiple of dollar per second.",
      "skos:prefLabel": "exponent of US dollar",
      "skos:scopeNote": "The factors for converting from one currency to another change constantly."
